During a phone call, President Obama and Prime Minister Hatoyama discussed North Korea, Iran, and the U.S.-Japan alliance. They condemned North Korea's attack on the ROKS Cheonan and pledged to cooperate with South Korea and the UN Security Council. They called on North Korea to end its provocative behavior and fulfill its international obligations. They also discussed Iran and the importance of ensuring compliance with nonproliferation obligations. The leaders emphasized the significance of the U.S.-Japan alliance, expressing their commitment to strengthen cooperation under the U.S.-Japan Treaty of Mutual Security and Cooperation. They were satisfied with progress made in relocating the Marine Corps Air Station Futenma and looked forward to meeting at upcoming international meetings in Canada.